<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="500" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1555,1696]" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">
The male genitalia and wing patterns of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley &amp; Godfrey" authorityYear="1921" box="[602,674,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="critias">
<emphasis box="[602,674,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">critias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[728,854,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis box="[728,854,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[869,974,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[345,1243,190,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[345,1243,181,1893]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male genitalia of A—Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. (northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province); B—R. l. crystallina Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. (central Vietnam, Thua Thien Hue province); C—R. l. critias Riley &amp; Godfrey, (southern China, southern Yunnan)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556624/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">Figures 9</figureCitation>
A-C) are highly similar. Thus, the former name must be regarded as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[689,815,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis box="[689,815,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described as a subspecies of the new valid species name. The most important character separating 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riley &amp; Godfrey" authorityYear="1921" box="[691,763,1628,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="critias">
<emphasis box="[691,763,1628,1653]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">critias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other subspecies is the absence of the eye spot in cell M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[176,184,1682,1696]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="500">3</subScript>
on the underside of the hindwing.
</paragraph>
